HEADWORD: Discompany
<hw>Dis*com"pa*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To free from
company; to dissociate.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It she be alone now, and <qex>discompanied</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>B.
Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discomplexion</ent>⟦br⟧
